01

Eleven new cases were confirmed except in Hubei Province

The 14th, January twenty-one.

It was an odd day, with thunder in the morning, light rain in the morning and a temperature of nearly 19 degrees at noon. It's windy again at night. It's like a bunch of people crying. Some of the car alarms won't stop. It's very restful.

The 14th is destined to be a Valentine's Day without flowers.

Valentine's Day in 2020, not to mention romantic gifts, sweet flowers, even out to eat hot pot has become extravagant hope.

Vegetables with the word "flower" , such as Broccoli and cauliflower, are hot items on Valentine's Day, according to Meituan's order statistics.

The Kunming branch of China Railway Express said demand for Valentine's Day flowers dropped sharply this year compared with last year, with the total weight only accounting for about 13 percent of last year.

Let's take a look at the numbers for new pneumonia.

A total of 2,641 new confirmed cases, 849 new severe cases, 143 new deaths (139 in Hubei, 2 in Henan, 1 in Beijing and 1 in Chongqing) and 2,277 new suspected cases were reported nationwide Thursday.

As of the 14th, there were 56,873 confirmed cases (including 11,053 serious cases) , 8,096 cured cases, 1,523 dead cases, 66,492 confirmed cases and 8,969 suspected cases.

There were 221 newly confirmed cases in the whole country except Hubei, which was the 11th consecutive day of decline. In the past, 890 cases had 3 days, 731 cases had 4 days, 707 cases had 5 days, 696 cases had 6 days, 558 cases had 7 days, 509 cases had 8 days, 444 cases had 9 days, 381 cases had 10 days, 377 cases had 11 days, 312 cases had 12 days, 267 cases had 13 days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There were 2,420 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (1,923 in Wuhan) , 912 newly cured cases (486 in Wuhan) , 139 new deaths (107 in Wuhan) and 48,175 confirmed cases (34,289 in Wuhan) , including 10,152 severe cases (8,335 in Wuhan) .

Deaths are on the rise, but prevention and control measures are getting tighter.

02

Public Health Emergency Management System

On the 14th, the Central Reform Commission proposed: To ensure the safety of people's lives and health, is a major task of our party governance.

On the one hand, we should base ourselves on the current situation and win the prevention and control of the epidemic with scientific precision. On the other hand, we should take a long-term perspective, sum up our experience and draw lessons from it. In view of the shortcomings and shortcomings revealed by this epidemic, we should take prompt steps to remedy the shortcomings, plug the loopholes and strengthen the weak points. We should persist in this course, the consummation, the establishment, the implementation, consummates the major epidemic situation prevention and control system mechanism, consummates the National Public Health Emergency Management System.

Before the SARS epidemic in 2003, China pursued "Economic Growth" ; after 2003, it emphasized Scientific Outlook on Development, pursuing "economic development" and harmony between man and nature. Since 2012, when China has stressed environmental protection, blue skies and white clouds have increased.

Through this"new coronary pneumonia", the proposal takes the National Health Protection as the work key point. This is a rational extension of governance, that is, "our party governance of a major task. ".

Therefore, a sound National Public Health Emergency Management System is a matter of course.

"scholar + official" has done very successfully is Huang Qifan. I've been learning from him.

More recently, Huang Qifan has come up with three valuable pieces of advice for public health and safety. We hope relevant departments will adopt it.

The first suggestion is that the Ministry of Education should encourage the establishment of high-quality public health schools in top-tier universities (formerly known as 985 and 211 universities) , rather than only medical schools.

The second proposal is to build a national key Single University of Public Health and epidemic prevention, such as the "China University of Public Health" , similar to the "University of Health and Human Services" and "National Institutes of Health Nih" in the United States.

The third suggestion is to increase the proportion of public health and epidemic prevention when governments at all levels formulate the 14th five-year plan. Between 200 billion yuan and 300 billion yuan will be spent from the central government to local governments to make up for the shortcomings of the entire Chinese public health system.

After this epidemic, we really need to focus on economic development, environmental protection and health protection together. Otherwise, the fruits of economic development will be eaten away by public health crises. Economic and social development will be set back.

In the absence of an effective public health emergency management system, our health care workers have suffered heavy losses.

As of 2400 hours on February 11,1,716 cases of new coronavirus pneumonia had been confirmed by medical staff nationwide, accounting for 3.8 percent of the country's confirmed cases, the State Council's joint prevention and Control Mechanism for COVID-19 reported at a press conference on Feb. 14, six of them died, accounting for 0.4% of all deaths in the country. There were 1502 cases of new coronary pneumonia in Hubei and 1102 cases in Wuhan.

Wuhan, Hubei Why occupy such a large proportion, the reason lies in the initial uncertainty, many medical staff in the "streaking" state, extremely vulnerable to infection. On January 20, academician Zhong Nanshan said that 14 medical workers in Wuhan had been infected, all from the Union Medical College Hospital.

In addition to Dr. Li Wenliang, several medical experts were also lost in Wuhan.

At around 2300 hours on February 7, Professor Hong Ling, a Chu Tian scholar at the Huazhong University of Science and Technology and a third grade professor at the Chinese Academy of Life Sciences, died of new pneumonia.

On February 10th Lin Zhengbin, a professor at Tongji Hospital, affiliated to Tongji Medical College, also died of pneumonia.

Within three days, two professors had also died of new pneumonia, devastating the Huazhong University of Science and Technology's high end talent pool.

Of course, artists die, too.

Liu Shouxiang, a professor at Hubei Institute of Fine Arts and a leading watercolor artist in Hubei Province, died at Wuhan's Jinyintan Hospital at 5 am Thursday at the age of 62 after suffering from pneumonia caused by his new crown.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu's daughter and son-in-law are also hospitalized with the virus, and his wife is in isolation at home, according to Liu's colleagues.

This is the archetypal "new pneumonia" -- the "connected model" : an old man gets sick, a younger man goes to the hospital and gets infected. Everything's fine. Everything's fine. Everything's fine.

Academician Zhong Nanshan said, "early discovery, early isolation" is the golden words that can save lives. So, close the cell, the tighter the better. It may be inconvenient, but you're a lot luckier than the guy in the hospital bed.

03

The Central Steering Group launched a general attack

On the 14th, Vice Premier Sun Chunlan led the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) to the Hubei Provincial Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters to implement the decisions of the Central Leading Group on epidemic prevention and control, and to further deploy and fight the Battle of Wuhan.

Sun Chunlan said positive changes had taken place in Hubei Province. But the situation remains grim. We should launch an all-round general offensive with more firm confidence, stronger will and more decisive measures.

The Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Command said that around the goal of "saving patients and preventing proliferation, " Efforts should be made to collect 100 per cent of confirmed patients, 100 per cent of suspected patients for nucleic acid testing, 100 per cent of fever patients for testing, 100 per cent isolation of close contacts, 100 per cent of residential villages to implement 24-hour closed management of specific measures.

Wuhan, NEW PNEUMONIA EPIDEMIC PREVENTION AND CONTROL headquarters issued a circular, clear residential areas closed management of the main measures. This is also the prevention and Control Command on February 10 issued notice 12, in the form of a formal notice, made detailed and clear provisions.

It used to be possible for a family to go shopping three days a person, but now it is not possible at all. It actually started with the "wartime management" of Shiyan Zhangwan District and then the Xiaogan Huanggang model. It is now in effect in Wuhan.

Notice requirements, the residential area to implement closed management, a residential area only to retain a single entrance. Old residential areas, open residential areas through the way to achieve hard isolation. The entrance and exit arrangement personnel on duty 24 hours, temperature registration, audit and release.

Other residents are not allowed to go out except for medical treatment, epidemic prevention and operation protection. District personnel in and out of all temperature measurement, registration. No outsiders are allowed to enter the residential area without special reasons.

It took 22 days to get from "closed city" to "closed community" .

While completely closing down the neighborhood, the districts are still O out, "fishing for people. " .

On the 14th, the Kong Hon, Qiaokou District and Hanyang districts also issued a public notice, announcing the collection of mail and telephone calls from the community not treated, not isolated "four categories of personnel. ". The recruitment targets of the three districts were the four categories of unadmitted and unquarantined patients, suspected patients, patients with fever and close contacts.

At noon, a netizen told me that an old couple had fever and had not been hospitalized. I advised him to hurry through the WECHAT APP "State Council Client" report. At night, he's in the hospital.

04

A number of cadres were disciplined

On the afternoon of the 9th, the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters asked Wuchang District to transfer 494 patients to designated hospitals by 12:00 PM that night. During the transfer of the patients that night, the work in Fruit Lake Street, Huang Helou Street and Luojiashan street in Wuchang District was delayed, the connection was disorderly, the organization was chaotic, and the follow-up service was not in place. As a result, the critically ill patients waited for a long time and then lost control of their emotions, to the people that we're dealing with.

On the 14th, the Wuhan Commission for Discipline Inspection gave a briefing on the serious accountability of those responsible.

For example, the Fruit Lake Street sub-headquarters is responsible for the transfer of 45 critical patients, but they do not pay enough attention to the transfer work, do not command properly, and do not give enough consideration to the critical patients, only two staff members and one guide vehicle and one transit bus will be arranged to carry out the transfer, and the preparation for the transfer road conditions, patients'conditions and the specific connection, etc. will not be sufficient and the response will not be timely, it leads to disorder of transfer process, disorder of organization, lack of follow-up service and long time waiting for transfer patients, causing adverse social impact.

In the Central Guidance Group after the interview, not only to or apologize, but also on the back of punishment. On the 11th, the Fruit Lake Street sub-headquarters Commander, Street Party Work Committee Deputy Secretary, office director an Jiyao was given inner-party warning, and removed from its Fruit Lake Street Office Director Position; Street sub-headquarters Commander, Street Party Secretary Jin Jiantao was given to admonish talk processing.

On January 20, more than 20 medical staff from the Jiangxia District Hospital of traditional Chinese Medicine in Wuhan and the First People's Hospital of Jiangxia district donated their blood 10 days after recovery, the blood was immediately sent to the China Biological Wuhan Institute of Biological Products and the Wuhan Virus Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences for relevant treatment, and the plasma with the required titer was inactivated, etc. , a novel coronavirus-free Plasma Product was prepared for clinical treatment.

On February 8, the first batch of 9 patients with severe illness were treated with plasma antibody therapy at the first people's Hospital of Jiangxia District Wuhan and the Peking Union Medical College Jiangnan Hospital. He's definitely getting better.

On the 13th, Zhang Dingyu, director of the Golden Pool Hospital, appealed to the recovered patients of new pneumonia to donate plasma.

In response to the overwhelming response from the public, plasma donations from several recovered persons were successfully collected at three donor sites in Wuhan on July 14.

What's going on here?

A study evaluating the clinical efficacy and safety of virus-inactivated plasma in the treatment of patients with severe new coronavirus pneumonia passed an ethical review at Golden Pond Hospital on Thursday.

Professor Zeng Fandian from Clinical Pharmacology, Tongji Medical College, Huake University, introduced the process of plasma donation for recovered patients with NCP

The whole blood is drawn, the plasma is separated, and the rest of the white blood cells, red blood cells, platelets and other substances are reinfused into the donor. This process, equivalent to components of blood donation. I'll give you back what you don't need.

I see.

These good news to the stock market, equivalent to the stock market "chicken blood. ".

Pharmaceutical stocks opened strongly on the 14th, Blood Products Companies Temple of Heaven Biology, bioluminescence, Bohui innovation all up limit. The investor that can not buy is dejected, the EGO that adds cang smoothly is full of ambition: "TEN BOARD START! "

On the evening of the 13th, a "new pneumonia patients with plasma containing antibodies, can effectively kill the new coronavirus, " the news spread, maxed out the circle of friends.

China biosciences, through its official public account, said that with the close cooperation of all parties, it had treated more than 10 critically ill patients with xinguantemian plasma. The clinical reaction was that 12 to 24 hours after the patients received treatment, laboratory tests showed a significant decrease in major inflammatory markers, an increase in the proportion of lymphocyte, an overall improvement in key indicators such as Oxygenation and viral load, and a marked improvement in clinical signs and symptoms.

"In the absence of vaccines and specific drugs, the plasma of convalescent patients with NCP is the most accessible resource for clinical-specific treatment, " the company said

That has focused attention on Temple of Heaven biosciences (600161 per cent) , the only a-share listed company behind Chinese biosciences.

05

Wuhan Alumni World Chu Shang

Chen Yixin, vice president of the Battle of Wuhan, urged Wuhan Alumni Tianxia Chu merchants to actively participate in the 2012 Olympic Games.

Alumni, as you well know,. For 40 years, Wuhan has 3 million alumni around the world.

Hubei businessmen originally referred to as "Hubei Shang" , always feel bad to hear.

After a large number of investigations and research, but also widely consulted entrepreneurs, academic experts, Chu Culture experts, administrative leaders of opinion, by Hubei Province Enterprise Development Promotion Association President Chen Xudong called ring "Chu Business. ". The first Chu Business Forum was held on 5 December 2010 at the Hongshan District Hall in Wuchang.

From July 22 to August 3,2011, the Hubei Federation of Industry and Commerce launched a campaign for Hubei businessmen to be named and named, with a total of 110,000 people participating in discussions and voting, a total of Chu Shang, Hubei Shang, Han Shang, Jing Shang, nine Shang, Crane Shang, Lake Shang, thoroughfare Shang, Hong Shang, Ying Shang 10 to be named.

The vote in favor of Hubei Merchants, known as Chu Merchants, was the highest. At a press conference held by the Information Office of the Hubei Provincial Government on October 8,2011, Zhao Xiaoyong, chairman of the Hubei Federation of Industry and Commerce, said that the unification of the "Chu Merchants" appellation is conducive to the calling of Hubei Merchants' brands, expanding the influence of Hubei merchants and promoting the economic development of Hubei.

From then on, Hubei merchants were officially named "Chu Merchants" .

Since then, every two years to hold a World Chu Conference, attracting investment fruitful results.

Chu Merchants are made up of three parts: those born in Hubei who do business in other provinces, those born in Hubei who do business in Hubei, and those born in other provinces who do business in Hubei. In fact, a section was added later: Those who had studied in Hubei were all businessmen from Chu.

That's a lot of power.

Chen Dongsheng, party secretary and President of the Hubei Chu Merchants Association, issued a mobilization order to the Global Chu Merchants to prevent and control new pneumonia at 11:00 am on the 13th.

Chu Business Prevention and control of new crown pneumonia leading group was established immediately, Chen Dong was promoted to commander-in-chief, Liu Baolin, Yan Zhi, Lei Jun, Wu Shaoxun, Mao Zhenhua as deputy commander-in-chief, Jian Hong as general secretary (General Coordination) .

As of 8:30 PM on the 14th, the platform has received 2051 donations from Chu Merchants and Wu da merchants, with a total amount of 691,709,900 yuan. The undiscounted medical supplies included 6597032 surgical masks, 533,000 civilian masks, 32,840 N95 masks, 201,204 protective clothing, 190,450 pairs of medical gloves, 260,000 pairs of gloves and 61,800 goggles, disinfection materials 303.3 tons, 40 sets of oxygen machine, 550 sets of thermometers, 3000 electronic thermometers and so on.

The Hubei Chamber of Commerce in Michigan set up the Michigan Support Group, and has received 1,152 donations totaling $175,234, or about $1.22 million, to purchase five batches of medical supplies and rush them back to Hubei.

Xiaomi group, Xishanju and Yunmi donated the XIAOMI tablet to support the remote video visiting system at Thor and Huoshenshan hospitals.

On the 13th, Lei Jun held an online press conference and released the Xiaomi 10 mobile phone.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lei Jun, a native of Xiantao County in Hubei Province who spent four years as a university student in Wuhan, said at the news conference that Lei was cheering for the city, choking up a little. When the epidemic is over, he said, he wants to go to the Wuhan University to see Cherry Blossoms and eat hot and dry noodles.

XIAOMI started emergency aid to Wuhan on January 23, including donations, N95 masks, isolation suits, thermometers, test strips, etc. , and later mobilized the relevant eco-chain companies together to continue to donate material aid, add in Lei Jun's $10.7 million donation, and the total comes to more than $30 million.

Wuhan also has alumni to thank.
